    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Jennifer Campbell and Paul Gries, two associate professors in the University of Toronto’s department of computer science (which is regarded as <a href="http://www.topuniversities.com/university-rankings/university-subject-rankings/2016/computer-science-information-systems#sorting=rank+region=+country=+faculty=+stars=false+search=" target="_self">one of the best in the world</a>) teach the series. The self-paced, self-contained Coursera courses match the material in their book, “<a href="https://www.amazon.ca/Practical-Programming-Introduction-Computer-Science/dp/1937785459" target="_self">Practical Programming: An Introduction to Computer Science Using Python 3</a>.” LTP1 covers 40–50% of the book and LTP2 covers another 40%. The 10–20% not covered is not particularly useful for data science, which helped their case for being our pick.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
